cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.OS, cs.AR, cs.NI 

This paper discusses the use of RDMA to improve the performance of distributed in-memory storage systems, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also proposes a new transactional dataplane using one-sided read and write-based RPC primitives, which relates to Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Operating Systems (cs.OS). The use of RDMA also involves network interfaces (cs.NI) and the paper discusses hardware-specific details, which could fall under the category of Architecture (cs.AR).
